      <title>Name Change Policy changed</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=SOE&amp;message.id=3986#M3986</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Originally it worked like this:  (KB answer 186)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color="#0000ff"&gt;Question&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color="#0000ff"&gt;If my rename request is granted, does it have to be posted on the website?&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color="#0000ff"&gt;Answer&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color="#0000ff"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000ff"&gt;Unfortunately&lt;/font&gt;, all renames will be posted on the website. This is to prevent players from generating a bad reputation intentionally, and then 'ducking' that reputation by getting a name change.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;All sound and logical. However, I asked where I would find the list and this is the answer:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color="#0000ff"&gt;We apologize for the inconvenience caused to you. However, this service is no longer available now. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I don't know why that 180° change happened. Whether too many scumbags canceled their accounts or SOE is thinking about moving into large scale character sales... *shrug*.  Just be careful. Characters can now simply change their name without leaving a trace.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
